text: What an achievement from Sunderland and Gus Poyet! Great to see the club stay up
Well done Mark Selby coming back from 10-5. Sad to see Ronnie lose though, hopefully return next year. Great Tournament as usual!

Absolutely outstanding by Crystal Palace! What an incredible season it has been
Tony Pulis Manager of Year in my opinion by a mile
Incredible frame of snooker between Ronnie O'Sullivan and Mark Selby. All square 11-11
Faultless performance from Chelsea . Rodgers could not unleash plan B as there simply wasn't one available. Liverpool still favourites
Superb from Ronnie O'Sullivan against Joe Perry in the Snooker. Great comeback, and surely favorite to win title again this year
#FBSCORE 1-1
Not a great game to watch but Chelsea looked solid as always under Mourinho. Costa with the only decent chance. Could go to pens next week
I bet Schwarzer did not think this point last year he would be playing in the semi-finals of the Champions league. Needs a huge performance
Favourites to succeed Moyes currently at MUFC: (Van Gaal 6/4) (Ryan Giggs 7/1) (Jurgen Klopp 10/1) (Diego Simone 18/1) Source: Sky Bet
Moyes Sacked. You can argue he deserved more time to develop squad but many performances were very poor and indicated no sign of improvement
Mark Selby beaten by Michael White 9-10 in World Snooker Championships. Certainly not at the level he has been in previous years
Dominant display from Manchester City against West Brom. Now 6 points behind Liverpool with 1 game in hand. Liverpool vs Chelsea = Huge Game
Forgot to congratulate Stanislas Wawrinka for his 3 set win over Federer in the Monte Carlo final. Hitting good form going into French Open
Moyes to leave Manchester United by end of May 2014 currently 1/7. Van Gaal favorite to succeed at 11/4. Source: Sky Bet
After two devastating seasons for Wolves, the fans finally have something to celebrate after becoming champions of League 1. Deserved that
Congratulations to Burnley FC for promotion to the Premier League!
Great tactics from Ferrer playing to Nadal's backhand. Deserved to go through but Rafa certainly not at his best. Even forehand was poor
Neymar should of made it 2-2 but Bale's decisive goal was superb. Barcelona's season destroyed in just over a week. RM still on for treble
I certainly had Palace to go down a few months ago. Once again a fantastic performance. Pulis manager of the year in my opinion.
Fantastic game at the Etihad. For me between Chelsea and Liverpool for Title now. Sunderland will do incredibly well to stay up.
Brave display from Swansea despite losing Flores early on. Chelsea proved too powerful in the end and clinched the match 1-0 from Ba's goal
Liverpool surely favourites now for the title. Passionate and powerful display from the team overcoming a strong Man city line up.
Epic F1 race in Bahrain. Fantastic driving from Hamilton and Rosberg both representing Mercedes. Thrilling race to watch!
Seppi too good for Ward in the end. Too many errors from Ward losing too many cheap points. Italy win 3-2 and progress to semi-finals
Superb performance from Everton in race for top 4. Everton simply wanted it more than Arsenal. More power, passion and precision.
Fantastic Davis Cup match with awesome atmosphere. Unreal shots from Fognini at times. Murray nowhere near his best. Italy level tie 2-2
Well played Murray. Levels tie with Italy to make it 1-1. Surely he will be playing in the doubles as well
Shame about Rooney injury. Hopefully will be back in time for Bayern. If not, it will be a huge blow for MUFC especially with RVP still out.
Shame about Benteke picking up an injury in training. I was looking forward to seeing him and Lukaku as a pair at the World Cup
Juventus with vital away goal against Lyon. Not the best game to watch, ref disrupting rhythm of game awarding countless free kicks
Dortmund  outclassed by Madrid tonight. However with Lewandowski, Gundogan, Bender, Subotic and more out it was always going to be difficult
Fantastic performance from PSG against Chelsea. Can "The Special One" and his team turn it around next week?
@Matty_Lowes97 It was 2-1 to united :)
Solid from Manchester United. Impressed with Carrick and Ferdinand both making crucial blocks/interceptions. Schweinsteiger unlucky with red
Djokovic seems to be getting back to his best as we get closer to Roland Garros and Wimbledon. Still think Nadal will win French Open
Liverpool absolutely crushed Tottenham today. Tottenham showed no passion or commitment. Very disappointing. Liverpool playing very well!
Fantastic start by Fulham, but Everton quality showed in second half with some inspired substitutions. Liverpool vs Tottenham should be good

Predictions for Premier League Games:
Liverpool 3-1 Tottenham 
Arsenal 2-2 Manchester City
What's your guys predictions?
What a Finish in the cricket. Well done England and Alex Hales!!!
